Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.16,0:00:05.33,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Its common name is Jackson's Widowbird.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.16,0:00:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The splendid love dance of the Euplectes\NJacksoni of the family Ploceidae
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.33,0:00:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,announces the season of love in the grasslands.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.70,0:00:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, what is apparently an elegant dance
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.01,0:00:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is in fact the painful struggle of history:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.35,0:00:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the bird must conquer a love partner\Nfor his reproductive needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.81,0:00:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us see, what is this "courtship"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.44,0:00:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Nature, not only a bird, but every animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.36,0:00:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,owns a private space, which is called its "territory."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.24,0:00:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When some unfamiliar character\Ntrespasses on those premises,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the bird reacts with fear and hostility.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.74,0:00:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, at the same time the subject feels
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.25,0:00:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a natural sexual inclination towards its reproductive instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.13,0:00:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to facilitate the innate reproductive needs,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.59,0:00:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is necessary to drive away this hostility,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.26,0:00:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that is the reason why
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.76,0:01:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the sequence of rituals called "courtship" manifests itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.85,0:01:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the ambivalent psychological tension\Nwithin the male bird grows even larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.90,0:01:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment when fear and hostility\Novercome the sexual inclination,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.90,0:01:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,namely, when the line of tension breaks down,\Nwe may see physical attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, the female runs, and as the male realizes\Nthat he has lost the possibility of copulating,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.41,0:01:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he develops an excessive impulse to attack which\Ndegenerates into creating devastation around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.42,0:01:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He attacks other males who are not related to the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.25,0:01:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or he concentrates on sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.84,0:01:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, many overcome this crisis
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.60,0:01:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and dedicate themselves to mutual display.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.23,0:01:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like the gulls, who bend their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.94,0:01:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or like the European storks, who clack their beaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.82,0:01:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or the blue-footed booby, who point to the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or the Eurasian spoonbills, who stroke their feathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.12,0:02:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However! In most cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.54,0:02:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's up to the female to choose her companion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.58,0:02:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the male must exhaust all his\Nresources in creating his display.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.63,0:02:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The golden palm weaver creates wonderful nests,\Nto which he invites the female.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.26,0:02:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The arctic tern shows off his economic\Npower by donating food.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.31,0:02:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The characteristics they want to display encompass\Nevery possibility without limit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.39,0:02:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from food resources to the beauty of shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.52,0:02:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the pressure from this sexual selection,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.24,0:02:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the male consumes all his energies modifying his body,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.41,0:02:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it more exuberant,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.62,0:02:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,more unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.87,0:02:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, his life depends on the effects of his display.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.38,0:02:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Even Confucius falls from atop the mountain of love."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.50,0:02:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Love is nothing but a frivolous joke."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.42,0:03:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Love is by its nature a weak promise."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.88,0:03:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Love among cousins is delicious like duck."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.51,0:03:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ways of male and female seduction\Nlook clear but indeed are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.77,0:03:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this was a story about seduction among birds!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.87,0:04:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say, "I love you,"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's nothing but another lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.05,0:05:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say, "Let's part,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's yet another lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.56,0:05:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man who runs in the sky becomes a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.28,0:05:38.46,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note. The man's tattoos indicate that he is a fierce yakuza.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.28,0:05:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the woman who floats in the sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.46,0:05:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko! I'm done with the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.00,0:05:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.67,0:05:49.68,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: A noren is a small canvas flap over an entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.67,0:05:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I pass through a noren, and everything's over...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.35,0:05:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I am, Grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.73,0:06:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had such a great bath, Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Self-given name: Yomota Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.87,0:06:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposed age: seventeen years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.42,0:06:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On April 2, 1989, she appears before the Yomota family,\Nliving in the Sumida area of Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.34,0:06:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She declares herself to be the granddaughter of Yomota's\Nson, Inumaru, also seventeen years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.42,0:06:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And ever since that day, she lives with that family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.97,0:06:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing about her past, where she came from,\Nor her birth date, is known.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She takes over the management of the family's affairs,\Nafter the mother, Mrs. Tamiko, leaves the Yomota house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.56,0:06:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a tendency to waste money, but despite this,\Nshe gets along very well with the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.69,0:06:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On April 20th of the same year, thanks to selling the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and with a loan against future earnings as base funds,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.53,0:06:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they buy a house in the Makuhari area of\NChiba prefecture, where they go to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears they borrowed large amounts\Nof money from a local financial society.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the 28th of the same month, an otherwise unidentified\Nman, calling himself a "Time Patroller,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.21,0:07:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,suddenly invades the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.38,0:07:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From a discussion of how to treat the suspect girl,\Nmatters escalate into a violent fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.22,0:07:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The son, Inumaru, hits the guy on the head with a metal bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.89,0:07:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He runs away, together with the suspect girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.72,0:07:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, they continue to wander, stopping in lodgings\Nhere and there around the capital, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:32.51,awadachisou,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fsp6\frz90\pos(540,160)}Adawachisou
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:32.51,awadachisou,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(480,410)\fs26\fsp1}Dog on\NPremises
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.56,0:07:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For six weeks now, they have been unaccounted for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.15,0:07:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, June 15th, they have a small room in Suginami,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:32.61,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Awadachiso is the name of the flower\NInumaru thinks he spotted in episode one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,called Awadachisou, where they live together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.08,0:07:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the report you asked me for, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.25,0:07:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No relevant news, huh,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.51,0:07:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about that girl's origins?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used all possible means to look for information\Non your son and the suspect, but unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.81,0:07:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you don't have to worry, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.47,0:08:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm already checking everything,\Nnot only the police fugitives list,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the estate agencies, but even\Nbars and fast food restaurants!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.77,0:08:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also taking care to distribute pictures of the\Nsuspects among my network of informants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.24,0:08:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, I'm using every possible means.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.32,0:08:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to tell you one thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.66,0:08:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If by any chance you're thinking of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.58,0:08:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,intruding in that apartment and dragging your\Nson back home with a couple of slaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.83,0:08:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I strongly suggest you forget the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say anything! I know perfectly well the\Nsuffering you're going through right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once he looked like a gentle and promising little boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, bodily violence and injuries, improper\Nrelations with a person of the opposite sex,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.98,0:08:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and moreover, a nightmare-like cohabitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.40,0:08:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is that girl's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.94,0:08:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That evil woman, that poisonous snake,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.23,0:08:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that swindler, that... that, that, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.74,0:08:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"However! If I were by your side...''
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.61,0:09:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If only I hadn't left home, things wouldn't\Nhave developed so badly..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.37,0:09:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.42,0:09:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that events have unfolded rather badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.01,0:09:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The suspect, in other words, the girl\Nwho calls herself Yomota Maroko,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.55,0:09:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,claims to be a granddaughter come from the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.64,0:09:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your husband and your son had\Nnot accepted this absurd story,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you, madam, would not have had to leave your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.98,0:09:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.61,0:09:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it would not have been necessary to buy a new house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.65,0:09:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither would it have been necessary\Nto fight with that weirdo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.24,0:09:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.11,0:09:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would not have been necessary,\Nafter that man had been knocked out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.99,0:09:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the young couple to escape secretly, as fugitives,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.58,0:09:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor for them to tenderly cohabit after that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A situation, or better said, a farce,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.96,0:09:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in which, although she caused all\Nthese troubles, she's accepted,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.39,0:10:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and trusted beyond any doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what on earth is the basis of this trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.47,0:10:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A birthmark on the butt, you said?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.23,0:10:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A star... a five-pointed star... how silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.23,0:10:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a butt-shake by a young girl, and\Nthose father-and-son perverts...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.86,0:10:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your son must have been charmed by the beauty of the girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.11,0:10:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and just pretended to believe her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.32,0:10:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, he doubts her origins.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.08,0:10:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But for your husband, things are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.70,0:10:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really believes that the girl is his great-granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really believes that he has a blood connection with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.67,0:10:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he has decided to dedicate the rest of his long\Nlife to this improbable as well as absurd story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.05,0:10:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why? How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't listen to me, even though\NI'd been his wife for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.47,0:10:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then just why did he believe such an absurd story?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.22,0:10:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For your husband, who slogs through a hard\Nlife every day just to protect his family,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,time travel, time machines,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.40,0:11:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or, more bluntly, an idiotic story that we can't even laugh at,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a leap from the routine of life, an unreal setting:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.41,0:11:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these are the reasons that your husband accepted this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.41,0:11:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So again, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.91,0:11:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let me put it this way. At times, people\Nwill, or better said, normally will
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,consecrate their lives to things typically considered fiction!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.72,0:11:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things that are ambiguous, uncertain, unverified,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.35,0:11:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the sources of an evil voice that foments aspirations
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.81,0:11:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which would not otherwise find a place in their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the heart falls asleep because of emptiness,\Nwhen it becomes tired of the routine,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the unreal floods toward us like a wave\Ncrossing an obscure marine surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.87,0:11:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and forms the wind of betrayal that steals our souls away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.75,0:11:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The word "possibility" is nothing\Nmore than an illicit expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.96,0:11:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a continuous whisper,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.17,0:11:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the tender wind that invites people\Nto exchange the true for the false.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone who is exposed to it at least once\Nwill end up burning in the flames of hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.84,0:12:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the martyrs, they will be lacerated in ecstasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.27,0:12:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to collect evidence of a reality than never existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.27,0:12:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is definitely the thing I hate the\Nmost and that I always feared,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.57,0:12:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the truth that "possibilities" are nothing\Nmore than words trying to shape reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must not tell them this until we have\Nre-established reality for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.83,0:12:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, you're saying that the only things we can trust
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.37,0:12:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the facts that we can see with our own eyes,\Nor touch with our own hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. Otherwise, in what do you\Nthink we should put our trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.46,0:12:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing I trust is this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.72,0:12:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth and facts can only be proved in the first place\Nby shapes that can be conveyed to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.69,0:13:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we put together a witness's impression\Nand words full of rhetoric and symbols,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the only thing we can obtain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.99,0:13:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is an unfocused image abased on the dream\Nmade by an uncertain creature like a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.99,0:13:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth that passes through a\Nlens and is impressed on film...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The record of the truth is made possible\Nby the cold objectivity of the optics.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.79,0:13:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe anything but these eyes\Nof mine, as they take pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.25,0:13:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I live as though the lens of this camera were my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.18,0:13:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think that's possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.80,0:13:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I trained myself specially for this purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the day I decided to be a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think we two can work it out perfectly?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.31,0:13:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, can I take your picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.91,0:13:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.53,0:13:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.70,0:13:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.04,0:13:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.71,0:13:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waaa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.08,0:13:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:03.43,awadachisou,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(210, 100)\fs20\fscy140}"Realistic"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:03.43,awadachisou,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(210, 140)\fs20\fscy140}Investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:03.43,awadachisou,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(210, 180)\fs20\fscy140}Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:03.43,awadachisou,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(210, 280)\fs20\fscy140}- Japan -
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.02,0:15:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up already!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.40,0:15:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say "I love you," it's just another lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.15,0:15:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you treat people so badly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.61,0:15:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.70,0:15:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop complaining so stridently and come out at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.20,0:15:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.71,0:15:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's nothing. I just wanted to say your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.05,0:15:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're funny, Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.92,0:15:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think so? Well, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.60,0:15:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's not the time to laugh! This is a serious matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.98,0:15:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the protagonist of this drama, I have to find a\Nbetter outcome, because I ran away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.82,0:15:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside this slice-of-life scenario,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that the drama of a young couple's passionate\Nlove would begin, or at least a big love story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.03,0:16:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the reason I also introduced into this home\Ndrama taboo elements, like violence...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.66,0:16:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what in hell is happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.12,0:16:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a boy and a girl run away from home and\Nlive for several weeks under the same roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one would normally expect something to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.68,0:16:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But instead, until now, there hasn't been a physical relation,\Nnot to mention a sentimental one, between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.05,0:16:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As matters stand, it seems that the drama will only feature
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a beautiful girl and her young grandpa,\Nwithout any loving passion between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.18,0:16:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So how can I allow the story to end up with a\Ntender friendship between two youngsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.57,0:16:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the plot twist of running away from home,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.24,0:16:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I would reverse the initial\Ntender, familial incidents,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.87,0:16:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.62,0:16:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have crossed a forbidden line,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.62,0:16:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have broken an unwritten rule,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have given myself a definitive last hit\Nas in the most classic of tragedies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.67,0:16:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was dragged into this cursed drama,\Nwith the purpose of telling {\i1}my{\i0} story,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.80,0:16:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but all of this was necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.51,0:16:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.68,0:16:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put an end to this story...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.89,0:17:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by showing that the reality of a bodily connection between\Ntwo young people is much more concrete
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.52,0:17:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,than the verbal promises of a blood relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.28,0:17:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.49,0:17:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.58,0:17:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.83,0:17:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.04,0:17:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind coming over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.71,0:17:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lights of the town shimmering\Nin the rain are so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.63,0:17:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.69,0:17:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much time has passed since we first met?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.28,0:17:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our fate is something really mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.70,0:18:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that until a few months ago,\NI was a simple high school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.87,0:18:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I've abandoned family and school,\Nand there's only you and me, Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.00,0:18:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I secretly live with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.96,0:18:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.79,0:18:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.67,0:18:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how Great-Grandfather is doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.38,0:18:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's forget about that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.68,0:18:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... perhaps we were wrong to run like we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.14,0:18:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, we had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.81,0:18:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, we should think about\Nhow we two will live from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.11,0:18:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.23,0:18:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ran away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.57,0:18:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have a place to go back to,\Nnor parents to count on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.95,0:18:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two of us are alone in this big world!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.45,0:18:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're alone, you and me, and we have to face the battle
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.45,0:18:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,against a grudging world that doesn't do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.50,0:18:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but sabotage the shining happiness of us young people!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.58,0:18:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And against the evil and useless old-timers'\Nlife that reality wants to impose on us,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.67,0:18:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we must fight a desperate and indiscriminate battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.68,0:19:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.01,0:19:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all because of me that you've ended\Nup in this situation, Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.10,0:19:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but Great-Grandmother and\NGreat-Grandfather as well... such trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.27,0:19:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I'd never came to this era...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.94,0:19:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, that's not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.28,0:19:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Grandfather. I was silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only wanted to meet you for a moment,\Nbut then I was conquered by your grace...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.95,0:19:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't imagine that it would end like this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.87,0:19:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.29,0:19:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.38,0:19:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.76,0:19:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.47,0:19:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much time has passed since we first met?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.77,0:19:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Maroko... M-Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.94,0:19:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.90,0:19:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.61,0:19:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, who until not long ago was a bother to my parents,\Nwill now go on living and taking care of your needs too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.36,0:20:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how Great-Grandfather is doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.45,0:20:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.45,0:20:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be doing great.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.33,0:20:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He finally got rid of his noisy wife and his bothersome son.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.66,0:20:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Against all expectations, he must be now enjoying\Nthe single life, like he never did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.21,0:20:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.13,0:20:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, we have to think about our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.67,0:20:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've run through all the savings we took with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.92,0:20:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't go on forever taking hot\Nbaths and being unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.85,0:20:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll start working!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.35,0:20:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried that I may have become a burden to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.73,0:20:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's so, then why did I come to this era?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.23,0:20:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.69,0:20:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But lately I feel like you've been trying to bear something...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.45,0:20:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, there are several things I'm trying to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.54,0:20:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, on our way back from the bath, I spotted\Na job ad on a public phone box in a small alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.75,0:20:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you young? Do you want to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.21,0:21:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll lend you clothes for work. You can\Nearn more than 10,000 yen per day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.76,0:21:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nursery available. More details at the interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.47,0:21:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hostess Club Ronpan."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.85,0:21:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.72,0:21:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I start working seriously, I'll at least be\Nable to provide for our basic needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.85,0:21:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Maroko, don't worry about it! I'm young too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.23,0:21:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do any job. I just have to choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.94,0:21:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow I'll start hunting for a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.74,0:21:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise you. So for now, let's go to sleep, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.66,0:21:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I've already taken too much advantage of your kindness!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.53,0:21:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been a fool! But now I'm going to do my best, Grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.70,0:21:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For my ancestors, for the Yomota family,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.87,0:21:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's my duty to contribute to the family income,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.67,0:21:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's my pleasure as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And also, they say I can meet fashionable\Nyoung men on this job...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.93,0:21:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sit back and relax, Grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.85,0:21:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise, I promise,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.06,0:21:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll conquer a rich young man,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.89,0:21:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and l will give the Yomota family back its splendor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.48,0:22:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When that day arrives, I'll go meet Great-Grandpa\Nand Great-Grandma,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.36,0:22:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you too, Grandpa, will be able to retire\Nand take your long-awaited rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.74,0:22:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.57,0:22:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not supposed to end like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.16,0:22:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.21,0:22:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.25,0:22:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.09,0:22:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.38,0:22:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much time has passed since we first met,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.43,0:22:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we don't have to worry about things like destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.18,0:22:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't even matter what the old man is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.85,0:22:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one problem now:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.27,0:22:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the fact that we two young people have run\Naway from home and are living together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.36,0:22:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at me, stare at me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.28,0:22:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,think only of me. Think of me as a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.41,0:22:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider me as the person I am, the one in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.24,0:22:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why? How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.08,0:22:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.71,0:22:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She calls me "Grandpa," and I answer "Maroko."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.71,0:23:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This encounter with a granddaughter the same\Nage as me shouldn't have happened at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.46,0:23:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I decided immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.76,0:23:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the moment we met,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.97,0:23:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by abandoning the family and the world, finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.85,0:23:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we would become a man and a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.10,0:23:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Grandpa...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.81,0:23:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to call me by name. By my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.39,0:23:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru. Call me Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.31,0:23:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Inumaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.44,0:23:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.74,0:23:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come back another time. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.20,0:23:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.12,0:23:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need any newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.62,0:23:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've decided to quit society.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.12,0:23:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.04,0:23:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have a TV either.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.67,0:23:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All we want is to stare at each other's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.88,0:23:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.50,0:23:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've decided to live in the present,\Nso we don't need insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.17,0:23:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said it's not about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.47,0:23:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what the hell do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.81,0:24:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here he comes, our hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.83,0:24:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bunmei! Damn you! Are you still alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.29,0:24:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bunmei? Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.33,0:24:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Loan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.96,0:24:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. Please let me give you my visiting card.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.25,0:24:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Receive with joy and repay with pleasure!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.25,0:24:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Loans always and anywhere, more than even necessary."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.09,0:24:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Murota Miyoki, of the Yoshimoto Loan Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.22,0:24:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what the hell do you want from me, you old loan shark?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.31,0:24:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About two months ago, our company lent
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.48,0:24:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,five million to Kinekuni Yomota,\Nin other words, to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.98,0:24:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, on the payment due date,\Nhe not only failed to show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.74,0:24:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he also ignored our reminders.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.91,0:24:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, in order to follow you\Nafter you escaped from home,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.28,0:24:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was fired from work, and he let his house go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.04,0:25:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.08,0:25:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great-Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.96,0:25:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were trying our best to find him,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.75,0:25:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but for now, I wanted to get at\Nleast the interest from his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.55,0:25:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never heard or met this Kinekuni guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.13,0:25:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, monkey, don't pretend you don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.80,0:25:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what? I ran away from home and rejected my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.47,0:25:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't take responsibility for that old man's actions!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.52,0:25:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a joke, monkey!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.69,0:25:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think that your familial situation can save your butt!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.48,0:25:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Thanks to their right of free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.19,0:25:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,people can decide to reject their wife, husband, or parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.12,0:25:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but, as living beings, it's impossible to deny the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.41,0:25:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that in the past, or in the present.\Nyou have been someone's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.12,0:25:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot deny, then, the concept\Nof a bond shared with parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.67,0:25:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your running away, your attempt to break the familial bonds,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.63,0:25:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is nothing more than the antithesis\Nof the conditions of reality!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.47,0:26:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you want to say is, "You can choose your\Npartner, but you can't choose your parents."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.39,0:26:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm saying, "At least pay the interest."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.31,0:26:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you ask me, I can't pay. I can't shit it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.31,0:26:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My job is exactly to make you shit it all out, monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.32,0:26:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That girl... with her cute face, we can squeeze her as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.49,0:26:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me... Don't tell me...!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.36,0:26:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I am telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.32,0:26:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.41,0:26:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I won't allow you to make Maroko an idol!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.08,0:26:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That has nothing to do with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.67,0:26:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, young and joyful girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.88,0:26:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you want to work in a cheerful place?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.88,0:26:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll lend you clothes for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.30,0:26:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can earn more than 10,000 yen per day!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.46,0:26:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nursery available. More details at the interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.51,0:26:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never allow it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.06,0:26:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think an anti-familial weapon like that\Nwill work against a sociopathic thug like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.31,0:26:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have you taste the cruelty of this world called life!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.11,0:26:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! A UFO!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.99,0:26:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.83,0:27:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go on interpreting your role,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.21,0:27:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's impossible to become the author of your own story.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.38,0:27:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now do you understand the bitterness of our times?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.87,0:27:46.90,Gosenzo,,0000,0000,0000,,Gosenzosama Banbanzai!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.92,0:27:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Opening Theme: "Gosenzosama Banbanzai!"\NLyrics and sing performace: Yumi Kojima\NSong production and arrangement: Kenji Kawai
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.00,0:27:54.00,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(200,310)\fad(500,800)}In Ambush!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.00,0:29:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru's father and mother, Kinekuni and Tamiko,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.17,0:29:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,reunite in an attempt to save their son from the kidnappers!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.96,0:29:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll also get to know the true identity\Nof Maroko, provoked by Bannai!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.97,0:29:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time! Gosenzosama Banbanzah episode 4:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.05,0:29:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retake and Counterattack, Retake and Counterattack!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.02,0:29:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you next time!
